      <title>ECM Website Development</title>
    </properties>
    <body> 
      <section name="Include the HST in your application">
        <p>The HST is packaged in two jar files, <code>hippo-ecm-hst-core.jar</code> and 
        <code>hippo-ecm-hst-taglib.jar</code>, both at version 2.01.00
          at time of writing. The core package must always be included, the taglib 
          may be omitted if you are not using actual JSP tags in your application. 
          When using Maven-2 as project build tool, add the following dependencies 
          to you <code>pom.xml</code>.</p>
        <source><![CDATA[<dependency>
  <groupId>org.hippoecm.hst</groupId>
  <artifactId>hippo-ecm-hst-core</artifactId>
  <version>[version]</version>
  <type>jar</type>
</dependency>

<dependency>
  <groupId>org.hippoecm.hst</groupId>
  <artifactId>hippo-ecm-hst-taglib</artifactId>
  <version>[version]</version>
  <type>jar</type>
</dependency>]]></source>
        <p>This requires also the repository <code>http://repository.hippocms.org/maven2</code>
          to be set up in your Maven-2 tool.</p>
         <h4>Dependencies</h4>  
        <p>Besides this direct dependency on the HST, the HST depends on these packages 
          (note that version numbers are omitted): </p>
          <ul>
          <li>geronimo-spec-jta.jar (or some other jar providing the Java Transaction API)</li>
          <li>hippo-ecm-api.jar</li>
          <li>hippo-ecm-repository-connector.jar </li>
          <li>jackrabbit-jcr-commons.jar</li>
          <li>jackrabbit-jcr-rmi.jar</li>
          <li>jcr.jar</li>
<!--          <li>jstl.jar</li> -->
          <li>log4j.jar</li>
          <li>slf4j-api.jar</li>
          <li>slf4j-log4j12.jar</li>
<!--          <li>standard.jar (JSTL tags)</li> -->
          </ul>
      </section>
